Proudwing500k@... writes:


&gt; Seeing no one, the dragon focused again on his spark feelings to
&gt; detect the bot. He concentrated, again seeing the estranged spark, but
&gt; this time, there seemed to be a feeling of amazement too. Focusing
&gt; even more, he discovered its nature... a decepticon female warrior...
&gt; and he felt her location.
&gt; 
&gt; He got out of his trance and flew quickly to the sides of the wounded
&gt; bot. He lowered his head as a sign that he was not here for war, but
&gt; rather for help.
&gt; 
&gt; AzureBlade: You are wounded, are you not? If you can hear me, I am
&gt; here to help you.

Standing at the base of the waterfall. She gazed at him for a moment, not in 
confusion or awe, but in serenity. 

&quot;Wounded?&quot; she finally spoke. Her voice like as always, deep, sophisticated 
femme voice with a fine mix command & soft gentleness. 

Indeed, the waters she was in were healing her. Slowly, though. Her wings 
however, would be a while to repair or they will have to be replaced. 

She only stood there, gazing at the blue dragon. 

